      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOTFEELINGSYOUKNOW (6) was last seen when a brave fourth to superstar Keayang Zahara in a Great Southern Star heat. He had been racing well in some good company prior including a third in the Shepparton Cup and fourth in the Kilmore Cup. Runner-up to good mare Jilliby Ballerini the last time he attempted a standing start. Finds a winnable assignment. IMPERIAL MONARCH NZ (8) has chased Keayang Zahara in Group 1 races in his last two assignments, finishing a brave fourth in the Grand Prix last time after a midfield finish in the Great Southern Star. He'll enjoy the class drop. ALDEBARAN ACRUX (9) has improved with each start this time in and comes off a last-start fourth at Group Three level at Melton two weeks ago. Should be hitting peak fitness. MORE WANTED (7) was strong in a last-start win by a nose in the Ararat Cup and starts 10m closer in the handicap. Respect.",
